        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              not only is holding down the shift key a violation of the DMCA, but not enabling autorun when you use this CD is as well.  Arbitrary and capricious laws are a great thing.  A further question is, is using the cd on a non-Win OS a violation of the DMCA (as it circumvents the copy-protection)?  <BR><BR>What do you mean there is no such thing as Fair-Use??  Fair-Use has been upheld by many courts and is in fact embeded in  <A HREF="http://www4.law.cornell.edu/uscode/17/107.html" TARGET=_blank>US Code</A>.  Note that Part 4 of that code states that the effect of the copying on the potential market is a factor to be taken into consideration for determination of fair use.  That's why copying things on VHS is basically legal, assuming you are not redistributing for profit, because it has little to no impact on the market.  Now, there are way too many confounding factors to say whether file-sharing has significantly impacted the market (some of these factors are economic decline/decreased consumer spending, consolidation of radio ownership, homogenization of what is played on those radio stations, decreased number of new artists released, etc) thus Fair Use may very well be applicable, or may very well not be.  nevertheless, it does exist.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
