          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              No, it's still a sale.  You can listen to it, sell it, microwave it, whatever you want...just not copy or rent it.  Both of those are straight-up infringement under USC 17, no way around it.  FU will (probably) indemnify you WRT private copying, and renting can be circumvented (see kangarooski's A/V Club thread), but you have absolutely zero recourse if these become technologically illegal.  In fact, it's no different than if they removed your ability to microwave it.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
