              EMI Canada uses a much more effective means of protection, and being an iPod user they have told me in no uncertain terms that they don't want my business. I think I passed on at least 10 CDs in the last 3 months thanks to their great protection method, what a winning idea! To make the matters worse, these not-really-CDs are being sold at the same price as regular CDs - why should I pay the same amount of money for an inferior product? And some of the bands they "protected" (like Asian Dub Foundation) are themselves outraged by it! More info from EMI at:<BR><BR><A HREF="http://www.emimusic.info/ca_EN/" TARGET=_blank>http://www.emimusic.info/ca_EN/</A><BR><BR>I encourage all Canadians to complain by going to:<BR><BR><A HREF="http://www.emimusic.ca/contact.asp" TARGET=_blank>http://www.emimusic.ca/contact.asp</A><BR><BR>(make sure to select the last field from the drop box).

              

              
              
